tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows markedly elevated creatinine, proteinuria, hematuria, and abnormal urine findings (cloudy, brown, low specific gravity, ketonuria, bilirubinuria), suggesting significant renal dysfunction, possibly acute or chronic kidney disease. Anemia is present (low hemoglobin, hematocrit), and HbA1c is low, ruling out chronic hyperglycemia. No evidence of infection in urine. Urgent nephrology evaluation is recommended for further assessment and management.
